mean_en: to gradually grow or become bigger, more advanced, stronger, etc.; to make something do this; to think of or produce a new idea, product, etc. and make it successful; to begin to have something such as a disease or a problem; to start to affect somebody/something; to start to have a skill, ability, quality, etc. that becomes better and stronger; to become better and stronge
sentence: We can watch the seed develop into a plant.
sentence_trans: 我们能够观察到这颗种子发育为一株植物的过程。
word_etyma: de不 + velop盖上 → 不阻止，不掩盖 → develop发展
